description: The number of new infections has fallen significantly in Germany, where testing is at a high level.
title: Coronavirus: Germany says its outbreak is 'under control'
title_page: Coronavirus: Germany says its outbreak is 'under control' - BBC News
maintext: Germany's network of diagnostic labs has been praised internationally for having responded rapidly to the pandemic. By early April Germany was doing more than 100,000 swab tests daily, enabling more coronavirus carriers to be traced than in other EU countries.
